  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Involvement of People with Disabilities in Electoral Process</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Moldova governement, local public authorities, journalists, media outlets, people with disabilities</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Providing support for the Central Election Commission to develop and promote regulations on access for persons with disabilities in electoral processes

Information and sensitization of political parties on issues of persons with disabilities and mobilize parties in solving such issues

Informing the media about communicating with people with disabilities and approaching the issue of disability</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support the Central Election Commission in drafting regulations for access to people with disabilities to the electoral processes; 

Develop strategic objectives to political parties containing recommendations on solving the problems faced by people with disabilities; 

Develop disability card commitments. Charter will be presented to political parties to be signed and respected; 

Analysis of the platforms of political parties from the perspective of persons with disabilities; 

Develop a set of recommendations for journalists on the proper language to be used by them when addressing people with disabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
